  "teacherScripts": {
    "slide_1": {
      "ops": [
        {
          "attributes": {
            "underline": true
          },
          "insert": "Start by clapping 5 times then use fingers to count."
        },
        {
          "insert": "\n\n\n"
        }
      ]
    },
    "slide_2": {
      "ops": [
        {
          "attributes": {
            "underline": true
          },
          "insert": "Circle/point to the sheep."
        },
        {
          "insert": "\n\n"
        },
        {
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true,
            "bold": true
          },
          "insert": "What do you see? I see sheep"
        },
        {
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          },
          "insert": "! Are the sheep "
        },
        {
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true,
            "bold": true
          },
          "insert": "sad or glad"
        },
        {
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          },
          "insert": "? The sheep are glad! Let’s count the sheep."
        },
        {
          "insert": " \n"
        }
      ]
    },
    "slide_3": {
      "ops": [
        {
          "attributes": {
            "underline": true
          },
          "insert": "Write numbers under the sheep while counting. "
        },
        {
          "insert": "\n"
        },
        {
          "attributes": {
            "italic": true
          },
          "insert": "One sheep, two sheep, three sheep, four sheep, five sheep! Can you count the sheep? Write and count!"
        },
        {
          "insert": " "
        },
        {
          "attributes": {
            "bold": true
          },
          "insert": "   "
        },
        {
          "insert": "\n"
        },
        {
          "attributes": {
            "underline": true
          },
          "insert": "Encourage student to count and write numbers. "
        },
        {
          "attributes": {
            "underline": true,
            "bold": true
          },
          "insert": " "
        },
        {
          "insert": "\n"
        }
      ]
    }
  },
  "teacherTips": {
    "moduleStart": {
      "ops": [
        {
          "insert": "- You can count with their body by clapping five times, then counting with the hand by showing five fingers. Alternatively, tap your head and shoulders!\n- If the student is too young to write the numbers, the item can be circled while counting. \n- Remember to erase the notations you make before the students turn to count, write or circle.    \n- Put emphasis on the “S” in cats so student understands that the word changes when there is more than one. \n\n"
        }
      ]
    }
